definitions.definition: An Alpine castle in Aargau canton, northern Switzerland .

A Swabian noble family named after it, which became the ruling (hereditary) dynasty of Austria , at times other countries (mainly in Iberia and the former Burgundian territories) and supplied successive (elected) emperors of the Holy Roman Empire .

main_definition: An Alpine castle in Aargau canton, northern Switzerland .
secondary_definitions: A Swabian noble family named after it, which became the ruling (hereditary) dynasty of Austria , at times other countries (mainly in Iberia and the former Burgundian territories) and supplied successive (elected) emperors of the Holy Roman Empire .

definitions.definition: A member of the Habsburg noble family.

main_definition: A member of the Habsburg noble family.
